Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
pull_block_constraint(25.10)                      pull_block_constraint(25.10)

Name
       pull_block_constraint - Pulls the routing constraints stored on the in-
       terface  nets  of  blocks in a design, to their corresponding top-level
       nets

Syntax
       pull_block_constraint

       [-help]

       [-file <report_file_name>]

       [-override]

       {-all_blocks | -block <list_of_blocks> |  -inst  <list_of_instances>  |
       -cellview {<list_of_libName_cellName_viewName>}}

       Pulls the routing constraints stored on the interface nets of blocks in
       a  design,  to  their corresponding top-level nets. The pull_block_con-
       straint command uses a two-pass approach  to  handle  conflicting  con-
       straints  on the same net. In this approach, the  pull_block_constraint
       command detects block-level and top-level conflicts and reports a warn-
       ing.

       If the -override parameter is not specified (non-override mode)  and  a
       block-level conflict is detected, no constraints are pulled.

       If    the   -override   parameter   is   specified   (override   mode),
       pull_block_constraint reports the conflicts but pulls  the  constraints
       such that the lower-level net constraints override any constraints that
       might exist on the top-level nets..

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each pull_block_constraint parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man pull_block_constraint

       -cellview {<list_of_libName_cellName_viewName>}
              Specifies the list of library, cell, and view names  from  which
              the constraints need to be pulled.

       -file <report_file_name>
              Specifies  the report file name. Given that the standard out re-
              port is in the abbreviated format, more details are written  out
              in this mode indicating:

              * The  lower, and upper level net names, the type of constraints
                pulled.

              * All the associated parameters.

              * Any conflicts that need to be resolved.

              * Which constraint were written to a particular net.

              Default: dumpPullInfo.log

       -override
              When specified, the lower-level net  constraints  will  override
              any constraints that might exist on the top-level nets.

              Default: off

       -all_blocks
              Specifies  that  constraints  with  hierarchical  scope  will be
              pulled from all blocks in the design.

       -block <list_of_blocks>
              Defines the list of block names of the instances in  the  design
              for  which  the  constraints  with  hierarchical  scope  will be
              pulled.

       -inst <list_of_instances>
              Defines the instances in the design for  which  the  constraints
              with hierarchical scope will be pulled.

Examples
              * Using  the  following  command, the constraints on the pins in
                the cellview binded to the block macro of all  the  instantia-
                tions  of  the  block  list  pll_clock and pwr_monitor will be
                pulled up to the top-level  nets  connected  to  the  instance
                pins.

                pull_block_constraint -block {pll_clock pwr_monitor}

              * Using  the  following  command, the constraints on the pins in
                the cellview binded to the macro instance I1/I2 will be pulled
                up to the nets connected to the pins of the instance.

                pull_block_constraint -inst {I1/I2}

